"software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 27}, "context": "This aspect of the WebAudio API is not compatible with the goal to support synchronous, 'just in time' interaction between hosts and plugins on the audio thread as in native plugin environments. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.295608520507812e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010793209075927734}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.707408905029297e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.4892852306365967}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036696791648864746}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.707408905029297e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "implicit", "software-name": {"rawForm": "host", "normalizedForm": "host", "offsetStart": 26, "offsetEnd": 30}, "context": "This is the case when the host is written as an Audio Worklet (AW) and when plugins are also AW based. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.08011519908905029}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006011724472045898}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.08011519908905029}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006011724472045898}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 38}, "context": "Furthermore, the parts of the WebAudio API having to do with parameters were conceived before developers had any direct access to the audio thread, forcing parameter updates to be scheduled asynchronously from the main thread far enough in advance to account for crossing the thread barrier. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.4892852306365967}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036696791648864746}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.6954879760742188e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.4892852306365967}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036696791648864746}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.707408905029297e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Web Audio", "normalizedForm": "Web Audio", "offsetStart": 48, "offsetEnd": 57}, "context": "In 2015 Jari Kleimola and Oliver Larkin created Web Audio Modules (WAM) [2], a standard for creating reusable and interoperable plugins implemented as WebComponents, the core of which was written in C/C++. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00011110305786132812}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.45226866006851196}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.103515625e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00015819072723388672}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.45226866006851196}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.103515625e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Web Audio Modules", "normalizedForm": "Web Audio Modules", "offsetStart": 48, "offsetEnd": 65}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0", "offsetStart": 66, "offsetEnd": 69}, "context": "Since then, this standard has evolved in a new \"Web Audio Modules 2.0\" version [1], taking into account feedback from developers of the first version and the evolution of web standards (with WebAssembly, WebComponents, WebMidi etc.). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00025957822799682617}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036481618881225586}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.534027099609375e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00025957822799682617}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036481618881225586}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.534027099609375e-05}}, "references": [{"label": "[1]", "normalizedForm": "[1]", "refKey": 1, "offsetStart": 1662, "offsetEnd": 1665}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Audio Worklet (AW)", "normalizedForm": "Audio Worklet (AW)", "offsetStart": 48, "offsetEnd": 66}, "context": "This is the case when the host is written as an Audio Worklet (AW) and when plugins are also AW based. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.08011519908905029}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006011724472045898}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.08011519908905029}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006011724472045898}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AmpedStudio", "normalizedForm": "AmpedStudio", "offsetStart": 51, "offsetEnd": 62}, "context": "We have been working with a developer's version of AmpedStudio and managed to load successfully some WAM 2.0 plugins in it. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0019205808639526367}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9871067404747009}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0019205808639526367}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9871067404747009}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioParams", "normalizedForm": "AudioParams", "offsetStart": 52, "offsetEnd": 63}, "context": "However, as mentioned before the automation API for AudioParams is not useful for many WAM design patterns, and we wanted to show how WAM supports sample-accurate processing of other kinds of events such as MIDI messages or parameter automation messages. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0027762651443481445}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.030494868755340576}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.3113021850585938e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0027762651443481445}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.030494868755340576}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001925826072692871}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio", "offsetStart": 54, "offsetEnd": 62}, "context": "Some WAM design patterns do not make use of any stock WebAudio API nodes, and while it is possible to define custom parameters for AudioWorklet, in many cases it would be too heavy / cumbersome to expose the potentially hundreds of parameters residing in WebAssembly code via that API. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00019806623458862305}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00023740530014038086}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7523765563964844e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.4892852306365967}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0036696791648864746}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.707408905029297e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio API", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio API", "offsetStart": 54, "offsetEnd": 66}, "context": "belongs to Spotify, and is mainly based on high level WebAudio API nodes, and is not open to third-party plugins. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.020784974098205566}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.001128852367401123}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0361180305480957}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.020784974098205566}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00839388370513916}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0361180305480957}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WamParameter", "normalizedForm": "WamParameter", "offsetStart": 61, "offsetEnd": 73}, "context": "To get around these limitations the WAM standard has its own WamParameter API to handle parameter updates, designed to facilitate many different WAM design patterns and interaction between hosts and plugins on either thread.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002186894416809082}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0030058622360229492}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.1576881408691406e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002186894416809082}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0030058622360229492}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.1576881408691406e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioParams", "normalizedForm": "AudioParams", "offsetStart": 62, "offsetEnd": 73}, "context": "The WebAudio API does allow for sample-accurate scheduling of AudioParams, and this capability is leveraged in the WAM SDK to facilitate WAMs that incorporate one or more stock Web Audio nodes. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00015819072723388672}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.000525057315826416}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.5033950805664062e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0027762651443481445}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.030494868755340576}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001925826072692871}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioWorklet", "normalizedForm": "AudioWorklet", "offsetStart": 67, "offsetEnd": 79}, "context": "None of the open source DAWs have their core audio player based on AudioWorklet, and only AmpedStudio.com ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004624605178833008}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.653236389160156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004987716674804688}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004624605178833008}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00023740530014038086}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004987716674804688}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioWorklets", "normalizedForm": "AudioWorklets", "offsetStart": 68, "offsetEnd": 81}, "context": "WAM v2.0 creators asked us to develop some host examples written as AudioWorklets (AW), with and without the use of WebAssembly modules, to show some features of the standard, in particular how WAM events can be used to automate a large amount of plugin parameters without leaving the audio thread (this is the case when both the host and plugins are written as AW running in the audio thread).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.14077019691467285}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05443388223648071}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.574920654296875e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.14077019691467285}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.05443388223648071}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.574920654296875e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioMass 4", "normalizedForm": "AudioMass 4", "offsetStart": 77, "offsetEnd": 88}, "context": "or waveform-playlist 3 , and some audacity like audio buffer editors such as AudioMass 4 .", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00011229515075683594}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 8.58306884765625e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00011229515075683594}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 8.58306884765625e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Audio Worklets", "normalizedForm": "Audio Worklets", "offsetStart": 90, "offsetEnd": 104}, "context": "We have developed for the WAM standard an example of such a host: a very simple DAW using Audio Worklets to manage the audio buffers for each track. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.3736228942871094e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998334646224976}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.3736228942871094e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998334646224976}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AmpedStudio.com", "normalizedForm": "AmpedStudio.com", "offsetStart": 90, "offsetEnd": 105}, "context": "None of the open source DAWs have their core audio player based on AudioWorklet, and only AmpedStudio.com ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004624605178833008}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.653236389160156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004987716674804688}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.004624605178833008}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.653236389160156e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.03028041124343872}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio API", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio API", "offsetStart": 103, "offsetEnd": 115}, "context": "Since the WAM standard aims to allow maximum flexibility for developers, WAM authors have decided that WebAudio API's AudioParams should not appear explicitly in the WAM API. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00023704767227172852}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00039964914321899414}, "shared": {"value